            "creation_date": 1527397270,
            "body": "<p>Remember you can't use <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> String.format(\"%.2f\", maltRequiredString);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Because maltRequiredString is string. Correct coding is that you must use float in this function and for that you have to convert your string to float<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>float f = Float.valueOf(maltRequiredString);  \nString test = String.format(\"%.02f\", f);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You can also use this technique for  making it 2 decimal<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>DecimalFormat decimalFormat = new DecimalFormat(\"#.##\");\nfloat twoDigitsF = Float.valueOf(decimalFormat.format(f));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 50549147,
            "question_id": 50549087,
            "last_edit_date": 1527428041
        },
        {
            "owner": {
